Helaman Barlow was chief of the bordering towns of Colorado City, Arizona and Hildale, Utah . 
  He said he acted on the orders of the church's leader Warren Jeffs out of fear of losing his family . 
  Barlow said he did this because he feared the church would take his wife and children . 
  He has now left the Fundamentalist Church of Latter-Day Saints . 
  Jeffs is serving life in prison for marrying and raping two underage girls . 
 